{
  "stem": "12491.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in December of 1939-- or might have been beginning of January in 1940, we-- the two brothers and I-- had decided some-- one of us has to go back and try to bring my mother and my sister out, in order to get out of the German rule.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We already begun to hear what is happening to Jews in the occupied part of Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of course, since I was the tomboy, I was the-- I-- I was selected to go.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I smuggled myself across the border and went back to Crakow.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] To retract here, when we left, September the 3rd, from Crakow, it was still summer.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was very hot.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the two brothers and I had only with us very lightweight clothing, sandals, no heavy shoes.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And winters in Poland were quite harsh.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I decided to bring my mother, my-- for my sister, and the winter clothing, whatever I can carry with, in big-- two big suitcases.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Again, across the river Bug.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But you had to smuggle yourself across the border.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was not something that you-- that you did, like you travel today, you put suitcases on and you-- and you go.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When you arrive, they give you the suitcases.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So but my mother and my sister would not go.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They thought that they are safer in their apartment in which they lived so many years.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Yes, there is anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But nobody-- at that point, at least-- is-- badgering them to the point that they would be scared.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "People believed that the war would be over in two or three months.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They decided to stay.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I had no choice but to take the two suitcases with all the winter clothing.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
